            "id": "malware",
            "instance": "163810b8-962a-4b04-ba1e-ba55c70b6954",
            "properties": [
                [
                    "name",
                    "ALPHV/BlackCat Encryptor"
                ],
                [
                    "description",
                    "ALPHV's proprietary ransomware encryptor — written in Rust for cross-platform support across Windows, Linux, and VMware ESXi — encrypts files using AES-128 or ChaCha20 per file, appends randomised extensions, and drops ransom notes linking victims to the ALPHV Tor negotiation portal. The encryptor accepts command-line arguments to target specific hosts or shares, delete VSS snapshots, propagate via AD, and wipe event logs. Deployed after full data exfiltration to maximise triple-extortion leverage."
                ],
                [
